{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:genesis.36",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Genesis 36 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:1",
      "text": "These are the descendants of Esau (that is, Edom).",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:2",
      "text": "Esau took his wives from the Canaanites: Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite, Oholibamah the daughter of Anah the son of Zibeon the Hivite,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:3",
      "text": "and Basemath, Ishmael's daughter, the sister of Nebaioth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:4",
      "text": "And Adah bore to Esau, Eliphaz; Basemath bore Reuel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:5",
      "text": "and Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. These are the sons of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:6",
      "text": "Then Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the members of his household, his cattle, all his beasts, and all his property which he had acquired in the land of Canaan; and he went into a land away from his brother Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:7",
      "text": "For their possessions were too great for them to dwell together; the land of their sojournings could not support them because of their cattle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:8",
      "text": "So Esau dwelt in the hill country of Seir; Esau is Edom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:9",
      "text": "These are the descendants of Esau the father of the Edomites in the hill country of Seir.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:10",
      "text": "These are the names of Esau's sons: Eliphaz the son of Adah the wife of Esau, Reuel the son of Basemath the wife of Esau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:11",
      "text": "The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:12",
      "text": "(Timna was a concubine of Eliphaz, Esau's son; she bore Amalek to Eliphaz.) These are the sons of Adah, Esau's wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:13",
      "text": "These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These are the sons of Basemath, Esau's wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:14",
      "text": "These are the sons of Oholibamah the daughter of Anah the son of Zibeon, Esau's wife: she bore to Esau Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:15",
      "text": "These are the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz the first-born of Esau: the chiefs Teman, Omar, Zepho, Kenaz,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:16",
      "text": "Korah, Gatam, and Amalek; these are the chiefs of Eliphaz in the land of Edom; they are the sons of Adah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:17",
      "text": "These are the sons of Reuel, Esau's son: the chiefs Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah; these are the chiefs of Reuel in the land of Edom; they are the sons of Basemath, Esau's wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:18",
      "text": "These are the sons of Oholibamah, Esau's wife: the chiefs Jeush, Jalam, and Korah; these are the chiefs born of Oholibamah the daughter of Anah, Esau's wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:19",
      "text": "These are the sons of Esau (that is, Edom), and these are their chiefs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:20",
      "text": "These are the sons of Seir the Horite, the inhabitants of the land: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:21",
      "text": "Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan; these are the chiefs of the Horites, the sons of Seir in the land of Edom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:22",
      "text": "The sons of Lotan were Hori and Heman; and Lotan's sister was Timna.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:23",
      "text": "These are the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:24",
      "text": "These are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah; he is the Anah who found the hot springs in the wilderness, as he pastured the asses of Zibeon his father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:25",
      "text": "These are the children of Anah: Dishon and Oholibamah the daughter of Anah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:26",
      "text": "These are the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:27",
      "text": "These are the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:28",
      "text": "These are the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:29",
      "text": "These are the chiefs of the Horites: the chiefs Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:30",
      "text": "Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan; these are the chiefs of the Horites, according to their clans in the land of Seir.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:31",
      "text": "These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom, before any king reigned over the Israelites.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:32",
      "text": "Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, the name of his city being Dinhabah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:33",
      "text": "Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:34",
      "text": "Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:35",
      "text": "Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the country of Moab, reigned in his stead, the name of his city being Avith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:36",
      "text": "Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:37",
      "text": "Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the Euphrates reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:38",
      "text": "Shaul died, and Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:39",
      "text": "Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died, and Hadar reigned in his stead, the name of his city being Pau; his wife's name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, daughter of Mezahab.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:40",
      "text": "These are the names of the chiefs of Esau, according to their families and their dwelling places, by their names: the chiefs Timna, Alvah, Jetheth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:41",
      "text": "Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:42",
      "text": "Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.36.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 36:43",
      "text": "Magdiel, and Iram; these are the chiefs of Edom (that is, Esau, the father of Edom), according to their dwelling places in the land of their possession.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
